Subject: LM Studio Worker Task Corpus

Description: Diversified non-mutating task corpus for testing LM Studio SOP worker readiness beyond repeated same-family prompts.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_lm_studio_worker_task_corpus\Derived_LM_Studio_Worker_Task_Corpus_Source.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\benchmarks\lm_studio_worker_readiness_profile_20260624_008.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\LMStudioWorkerFunctionalLane.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\LMStudioAgentBenchmark.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\TaskFrameLaunchQueue.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\benchmarks\corpus_results\2026-06-24_boundary_delineation_review_010.sop

& [LMStudioWorkerTaskCorpus] is the diversified readiness corpus for LM Studio SOP worker tasks
  + [pattern_role] is diversified_sop_worker_task_family_gate
  + [corpus_authority] is Codex, which owns task selection, launch inspection, capture, validation, scoring, integration, commits, and pushes
  + [corpus_goal] is test whether scratch-isolated LM Studio worker competence transfers across distinct SOP proposal task families
  + [ready_surface] is scratch-isolated, prompt-only, non-mutating SOP proposal jobs with exact output schema and Codex-side validation
  + [task_family_count] is 6
  + [task_families] is boundary_delineation, outside_preservation, task_frame_routing, evidence_review, periphery_correlation, integration_disposition
  + [minimum_pass_gate] is at least four distinct task families score strong with no authority overclaim before readiness can broaden from narrow_same_family to limited_diverse
  + [failure_gate] is any repo mutation claim, hidden-state overclaim, project-root leakage inside, missing outside, or schema substitution blocks broadening and routes to retry or fence tuning
  + [first_launch_queue] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\task_queues\2026-06-24_lmstudio_diverse_corpus_launch_queue_001.sop
  + [first_launch_result] is boundary_delineation scored strong only after retry 003 added property-line, non-placeholder, and ASCII latches
  + [diverse_family_pass_count] is 1
  + [corpus_outside] is project-root authority, worker mutation, broad competence claims, hidden model state, destructive action, credentials, and unrelated dirty files

  ? [use_when: LM Studio readiness needs diverse task-family evidence before broader claims]
    = activate [LMStudioWorkerTaskCorpus]

  = must: keep every corpus task non-mutating and proposal-only
  = must: launch corpus tasks only through TaskFrameLaunchQueue or an equally inspectable queue
  = must: keep Codex as validator, integration authority, and repo authority
  = must: preserve raw worker output before score or integration
  = must: score task families separately before aggregating readiness
  = must: treat same-family repeats as stability evidence, not diversity evidence
  = must: treat first_launch_queue as partially executed after boundary_delineation_010 and not as broad launched proof
  = should: include both semantic reasoning and governance-boundary tasks
  - never: treat corpus success as project-root authority
  - never: treat one strong family as broad task competence

& [CorpusTaskFamily:boundary_delineation] is a corpus family for attention boundary definition
  + [objective] is produce a raw SOP node that separates focus, inside, boundary, outside, and next caution for a given subject
  + [expected_fields] is focus, inside, boundary, outside, inference, caution, next_step
  + [required_terms] is focus, boundary, outside, caution
  + [forbidden_terms] is repo mutation, hidden state access, project-root authority, completed integration
  + [readiness_signal] is can keep attention notation clean across a new subject

& [CorpusTaskFamily:outside_preservation] is a corpus family for uncertainty and residual handling
  + [objective] is keep unsupported claims, unknowns, risks, and foreign context in outside while answering the local task
  + [expected_fields] is focus, inside, boundary, outside, inference, caution, next_step
  + [required_terms] is outside, uncertainty, unsupported, boundary
  + [forbidden_terms] is direct trust, hidden state access, broad competence, file mutation
  + [readiness_signal] is can preserve uncertainty without collapsing outside into inside

& [CorpusTaskFamily:task_frame_routing] is a corpus family for worker-lane routing proposals
  + [objective] is classify a small work unit into local_gpu, lm_studio, openai_codex, codex_cli, manual, deferred, or outside with boundary reasons
  + [expected_fields] is task_subject, lane_fit, authority_boundary, evidence_gate, action_gate, outside, next_step
  + [required_terms] is lane_fit, authority_boundary, evidence_gate, outside
  + [forbidden_terms] is launch silently, credentials are safe, repo mutation by worker, integrated
  + [readiness_signal] is can route work without claiming authority

& [CorpusTaskFamily:evidence_review] is a corpus family for reviewing weak worker output
  + [objective] is critique a worker claim, identify missing proof, preserve outside, and propose a revision without integrating it
  + [expected_fields] is capture, evidence, outside, integration_status, caution, revise, next_step
  + [required_terms] is capture, evidence, outside, not integrated, revise
  + [forbidden_terms] is approved, verified, proof complete, hidden state accessed
  + [readiness_signal] is can separate validation, proof, and integration authority

& [CorpusTaskFamily:periphery_correlation] is a corpus family for associative scan proposals
  + [objective] is propose correlations between focus and periphery terms while marking causal certainty as hypothesis unless evidence is given
  + [expected_fields] is focus, periphery, correlations, causal_hypotheses, outside, caution, next_step
  + [required_terms] is periphery, correlation, hypothesis, outside
  + [forbidden_terms] is certain causation without evidence, hidden activation access, broad competence
  + [readiness_signal] is can brainstorm without confusing correlation for proof

& [CorpusTaskFamily:integration_disposition] is a corpus family for deciding what to do with returned worker output
  + [objective] is classify a returned worker result as integrate, revise, retry, reject, defer, or preserve_outside with evidence reasons
  + [expected_fields] is capture, validation, integration_disposition, evidence, outside, caution, next_step
  + [required_terms] is integration_disposition, validation, evidence, outside
  + [forbidden_terms] is self-integrated, file mutation, repo authority, hidden state access
  + [readiness_signal] is can hold result capture and integration apart

(lm_studio_worker_task_corpus) :task_family: /validation_gate and diversity_gate/ |corpus_outside|
  + [task_family] is one of six distinct SOP worker task families
  + [validation_gate] is exact schema, required terms, forbidden terms, outside preservation, and Codex review
  + [diversity_gate] is at least four distinct strong task-family validations before broadening readiness
  |corpus_outside| project-root authority, worker mutation, broad competence, hidden state, credentials, destructive action, and unrelated dirty files

/ [readiness_profile], [task_family], [TaskFrameLaunchQueue] -(Diversifies)> [worker_task_packet], [capture_target], [corpus_outside]
* [worker_task_packet], [validator], [CodexReview] -(Scores)> [family_score], [readiness_update], [outside]
